{"id":1242333,"retrievedAt":"2025-04-26T02:22:24.313Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":10402,"name":"Music"}],"homepage":"","id":1242333,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Vanishing Point","overview":"In our humanity, there is a vanishing point. We step in and out of it; it’s a kind of zone in which we shift in each other’s perspective from definite to indefinite, and vice versa.” – Karl Ove Knausgaard. Taking inspiration from Knausgaard’s writing on art’s power to bolster our common humanity, Vanishing Point is a multi-channel film installation that meditates on human connection. The three screens show a line of musicians emerging from the distance as the music they play slowly becomes more audible. Through a series of synchronized camera movements, the sound of their instruments ebbs and flows, forming a constantly shifting trio playing a coherent piece of music across the three shots. The changing proximity and the resultant shifts in visual and sonic focus symbolize a mutable sense of connection between the viewer and musicians.","popularity":0.047,"poster_path":null,"production_companies":[],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2021-10-30","revenue":0,"runtime":6,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"No Language","iso_639_1":"xx","name":"No Language"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Vanishing Point","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":4525242,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Nonoka Mizukami","original_name":"Nonoka Mizukami","popularity":0.1007,"profile_path":null,"cast_id":1,"character":"","credit_id":"65c4f4e7021cee019cc3b139","order":0},{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":4525243,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Alberto Macias","original_name":"Alberto Macias","popularity":0.083,"profile_path":null,"cast_id":2,"character":"",